raw_data.description: Charlotte Mecklenburg Library is the library system serving Mecklenburg County, NC with 20 locations and a digital online site. Our mission is to improve lives and build a stronger community. We create a community of readers and empower individuals.
raw_data.typical_time_spent: People typically spend up to 1.5 hours here

reviews_data.review_text: Amazing library. Awesome kids section with lots of fun toys. Great story time. Awesome sale section (for books). And the librarians are so friendly and helpful!
Great staff. Very helpful.

I homeschool my children and have been to almost every library in this area. Never had an issue until I come to this branch. We have been here twice. The first time I was told my 1 year old needed to be quiet when he was playing in an area with multiple children who were all just being children. The 2nd time a lady wouldn't allow me to stay inside the class my daughter was taking. It was an art class! I like to be there so I can see what she's learning and converse with her afterwards more in depth. Again, no other library cares if parents stay in the class quietly sitting in a corner. Do better Mint Hill staff. It's  a library, not a prison.
I attended a "makers" class where we decorated seashells. The librarians were wonderful instructors.
A great source for research of both historic and current events!!
Friendly and fast service
Great Staff, several computer work stations for kids and adults. Watch out for early voting on Saturdays, the parking lot may be jammed with voters

I stopped by this library for the first time on Thursday, 04-25-24. I was immediately greeted by the staff near the computer station and the desk to the left of the door.

I spent a while here and was able to see the staff engaging with others. I enjoyed the open layout. The teen area was busy and occupied most of the time. The staff was patient as children attempted to check out books and shared their enthusiasm about school events. I'd definitely return when in the area.
Super friendly staff, they were happy to help 😁

This location in Mint hill is super amazing,  most friendly and knowledgeable staff, they are just welcoming and ready to assist in anyway.
Once entered, you will be greeted with a genuine friendly smile. It is always clean. The Liberians always putting back books and access making everything organized and perfect for the next person that walks in.To the right will be the kids area, lots of book, dvds, computer games and educational fun stuff on the touch screen monitors., kids have lots of fun activities and their own lounge, there is also a teen lounge as well a quiet room area. I visit here at least 3 times a week during the afternoons. Checking out book dvds or audio books were so easy, returning was just even effortless with drive up or inside returns.
Did I mention that the staffing is awesome, friendly and very helpful?
Beautiful place, very friendly and welcoming staff. Easy to find things you need.

We visit this library weekly and we really love coming here.The staff is always so helpful. We enjoy doing the weekly puzzles. I've been visiting 6 yrs now since my youngest started Toddler Play Activities. I love how clean, small and cozy it is. Since we homeschool it really meet all our needs for resources concerning our book selections. Also, the computer area is a plus for us. You won't be disappointed if you visit. Very helpful staff.

The Mint Hill library put on a memorial for my sonChris Spradlin tonite. I knew librarians were good people. His coworkers and friends were so kind and shared their stories about Chris. I will remember this for the rest of my life! Thank u Everyone!

I voted early here. There were lots of signs for people who were running for office. The parking lot was busy, but still had plenty of parking. The voting was easy to get to. It was easy to vote and leave. The volunteers were very helpful and friendly. Great experience!!
I went to the Mint Hill Library again today. A knitting and crochet group meets from 12-2 the
first Tuesday of the month. Everyone works on different projects.  Today, someone brought in cross stitch to work on.  It's fun to see what others are doing
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for voting with us, Carol!

reviews_data.review_text: Thank you 😊 nice library and nice team work
Nice place

I went in for the first time with my daughter and I can already say I won’t be back. Going through the first set of doors it smelled like car oil or some sort of oil or fume. Went in through the second set to the actual inside and the smell was still there and probably stronger. We weren’t there very long cause the smell started making my head and stomach hurt.
Everyone is so pleasant there! Love it!
Very nice staff.
Super helpful and friendly staff.
Very friendly staff
Not a big library but pretty nice.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks, Bruce! You'd be surprised at how many well-meaning customers try to re-shelve books on their own - at least, that's what we're hoping happened here. We'll try our best to monitor the shelves better!

reviews_data.review_text: I've been taking my kiddos here for 10 years, since we moved to Mint Hill. Lovely staff, always eager to help and get you the titles you're looking for. Now that my children are old enough, we all volunteer here to help pass the love of reading and learning onto our community.
Great library. Staff is always helpful and nice.
Love this place... I'm usually on the kid's side with my daughter in the ealry afternoon and it's never busy. Nice selection of books, good seating, pleasant & helpful staff. Highly recommended!
Entirely too much talking.  I thought conversation's in the library were to be whispered.  Very hard to stay focused and concentrate.
I was trying to feel out an application and I couldn't get gmail to load. Also could get into the application to fill it out. Customer service was great except for the issues I had with the browser.
The people are so respectful and ALWAYS help you whenever needed. No complaints whatsoever, and the process is so easy!!!!!
I love it
It was closed but the best library ever.

Nicest people, very helpful!!
User friendly,  very clean!!
Very nice people there.  Love the new carpet. It will be nice when everything else can be put back in place.
Excellent customer service!
I cannot say enough good things about the staff and service at my Mint Hill Library!

I agree with all those who say that this is not a place to read or study.   The NOISE LEVEL IS VERY HIGH.  People were on the phone, someone was doing interviews, someone was Skyping to another country.  I had to endure the conversation though I didn’t understand it.   I complained each time to the staff, but my complaint fell on quiet ears👂🏽. The staff is great but again DOES NOT ENFORCE QUIETNESS.

The librarians do an less than adequate job at reminding everyone that this is a quiet place for learning, reading, and studying.  This is by far the noisiest place I’ve been to in 5 states. People should know better and if they don’t, at a minimum, it’s the librarians job to advocate the rules of order in this place.
Great staff!... Very helpful and friendly!
Awesome library! We attend story time quit frequently and my son loves it.

The staff is very friendly and helpful but they don't do anything to enforce a quiet and calm atmosphere. Kids were literally running around the library yelling and laughing. Definitly don't come to this location if you're trying to study or simply read a book in peace.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi, Loretta, we apologize for this experience. We've forwarded your comments on to the branch manager at this location to each guest has a positive experience.

reviews_data.review_text: I usually only come in here to sit and read. It's a very quiet location with low "gaming chairs" all around the walls that let you tuck yourself into a little nook and hide away to read. It's a very peaceful library, which I can't say about some of the others in the area. I wish the access to it wasn't quite so odd.
Friendly staff

This is my favorite of the Charlotte Mecklenburg libraries. The staff is exceptionally helpful and friendly, and for those of us who frequent the library, they even greet us by name. If I can't find something or they don't have it, they go out if their way to get it for you.
The staff are so helpful and kind. I love that there are places in the library for someone to relax and read in peace.

The staff-- especially the computer staff-- are extremely helpful. But this is one of the loudest places in Mint Hill. Tutoring going on in regular voices, teenagers having regular conversations, librarians talking across the room to each other. Not a good place for quiet but staff is very helpful

We have been attending this library for years, since my five year old was ten months. The librarians are super amazing and truly care about kids. They also have great book recommendations for all ages, be sure to ask. I believe the storytimes and library programs helped my daughter to read before she turned three, she's now on chapter books recommended by them. I would give this branch a million stars if I could. Thanks to them my child has a passion for reading. And the homeschool programs are spectacular!
Everyone is super friendly at this branch. Always willing to go the extra mile. If they don't have something at this branch, you can order it to have it sent at no cost. I love the library.

The few times I have been to this library the staff as been very rude. They just sit around the front desk visiting. When I asked one of them how many books I could check out she said she didn't know. I have never disliked a library more.

Nice library to visit. Great set up for kids to play and explore books. Attended storytime for preschoolers and it was fun. The instructor was great! No sign up for storytime was needed at this location which was awesome. Would like to see a shorter self check out area for preschoolers to be able to perform the book check out process themselves.
This library has a wonderful staff group and environment. I come here once a week.

I like this library and frequently go here Bc it's close to home, BUT they allow too much noise. Libraries are supposed to be quiet and the talking is excessive. The Librarians don't even use inside voices when talking. It's very distracting when trying to do homework.
Fantastic place to visit. Great staff.
